{#-
  Executive summary partial (P6-C04b / ADR-306).

  Consumes the bare name `comprehension_questions` (ADR-307b). The
  renderer asserts `len(comprehension_questions) == 3` and runs the
  JARGON_FORBIDDEN scan on every question body before this partial
  is rendered; no defensive guard is needed here.

  Per ADR-306 the answer sits behind a <details> disclosure — jargon
  is permitted in answers (the disclosure pattern keeps the main flow
  plain-language while still surfacing statistical detail).

  NFR-4 / TC-NFR-4-01: block present, count=3, aria-labelledby wired
  to the heading.
-#}
<p class="exec-summary-lede">The executive summary layer carries the report&rsquo;s plain-language findings; statistical detail sits behind sidenotes and the methodology appendix.</p>
<aside class="comprehension-questions" aria-labelledby="cq-heading">
  <h3 id="cq-heading">Headline findings &mdash; can you answer these?</h3>
  <ol>
    {% for cq in comprehension_questions %}
    <li>
      <p class="cq-question">{{ cq.question }}</p>
      <details>
        <summary>Reveal answer</summary>
        <p class="cq-answer">{{ cq.answer }}</p>
      </details>
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ol>
</aside>
